trend_summary: Across the series the wooded, low-rise suburb maintains its character while the southern highway junction catalyses growth: office parks and large white-roofed warehouses spread outward, a few new cul-de-sac housing pockets appear, and forest edges recede slightly. Road widening and added ramps accompany this commercial expansion; otherwise the mainly tree-covered residential fabric stays stable.
notable_changes: Progressive enlargement of the commercial/industrial block south of the main interchange, with more large white-roofed buildings.
Addition and realignment of highway ramps and auxiliary lanes, improving regional connectivity.
New small residential subdivisions infilling former woodland and pasture in the central belt.
Noticeable thinning of forest cover along northern and western edges, indicating gradual clearing.
Minor riparian vegetation increase along the river, hinting at restoration or natural regrowth.
